X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Connect Mat-Su": "https://www.connectmatsu.org/event/organic-gardening-your-soils-health-care-plan/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:connect_matsu
X-SOURCE:Connect Mat-Su
DTSTART;TZID=America/Anchorage:20260421T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/Anchorage:20260421T133000
DTSTAMP:20260308T083557
CREATED:20260206T233702Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260308T162209Z
UID:10012808-1776772800-1776778200@www.connectmatsu.org
SUMMARY:Organic Gardening: Your Soil's Health Care Plan
DESCRIPTION:This is an in-person Organic Gardening class that meets at Mat-Su College in the Snodgrass Hall Building (SGH)\, first floor in Room 117. This course meets for 1 day only from 12:00 pm – 1:30 pm. Cost is $25. \nUnlock the power of cover crops\, green manures\, compost\, and mulches. Discover how to use and time them for constantly regenerating your garden’s vigor and production. The course meets for one 90-minute session. The instructor presents the material via a slideshow and with hands-on demonstrations.
URL:https://www.connectmatsu.org/event/organic-gardening-your-soils-health-care-plan/
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://www.connectmatsu.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/MSC-Soil-Healthcare.jpg
END:VEVENT
