SUMMARY:Valley CASA Preservice Training
DESCRIPTION:Make a difference in a child’s life! Alaska CASA is hosting preservice training for new Court Appointed Special Advocates from May 5–22\, on Tuesdays and Thursdays\, 6:00–8:30 PM\, with graduation on Friday\, May 22 at 11:30 AM at the Palmer Court. CASAs advocate for youth in the child welfare system\, ensuring their voices are heard and their best interests represented.\nLearn more and register today: www.alaskacasa.org
URL:https://www.connectmatsu.org/event/valley-casa-preservice-training/
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=application/pdf:https://www.connectmatsu.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/Valley-CASA-Online-Training-Schedule-Spring-2026-combined-1.pdf
END:VEVENT
